      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Various Daylife",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is a smaller RPG experience that provides an experimental combat system with the Cha-Cha-Cha system, although it is MP heavy on usage unfortunately, which doesn’t make for a fun early game. I feel like there would be more to explore in this franchise if the game wasn’t a port of a mobile release and was rebuilt for consoles with the basic functions like controlling your character in exploration or action input for the jobs, but alas, that is not an option. There is an interesting world to explore here but when you’re fighting through the micromanaging stat system, the lack of player input and the repetitive gameplay loop is enough to push most players away.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
